1
00:00:00,033 --> 00:00:01,400
(All characters, organizations,
and events in this drama are fictitious.)

2
00:00:01,400 --> 00:00:02,700
(Filming complied with guidelines
for children, youth, and animals.)

3
00:00:03,933 --> 00:00:05,033
(Kangsu Construction)

4
00:00:05,033 --> 00:00:07,000
What? What's the annual salary?

5
00:00:07,900 --> 00:00:11,133
It's 80,000 dollars.
If you add overtime and bonuses,

6
00:00:11,733 --> 00:00:12,900
it'll come out to around 100,000 dollars.

7
00:00:13,500 --> 00:00:15,433
The executive assistant's salary
is 80,000 dollars?

8
00:00:16,233 --> 00:00:17,633
Aren't you going overboard?

9
00:00:17,633 --> 00:00:19,200
Of course, I'd like to appoint you...

10
00:00:19,200 --> 00:00:21,433
as chief assistant like Gwon Sik,

11
00:00:22,100 --> 00:00:23,400
but now isn't the right time.

12
00:00:24,033 --> 00:00:26,833
Anyway, I trust you'll accept my offer.

13
00:00:27,633 --> 00:00:30,400
Of course, compared to the cleaning job
I'm doing now,

14
00:00:31,033 --> 00:00:33,333
the salary is tempting, no question.

15
00:00:34,400 --> 00:00:36,300
But I can't accept a position
and a salary like that...

16
00:00:37,000 --> 00:00:38,500
without justification.

17
00:00:38,633 --> 00:00:41,700
Justification?
Hey, I'm the CEO of Kangsu Construction.

18
00:00:41,700 --> 00:00:44,133
People like me don't need
to provide justification.

19
00:00:44,700 --> 00:00:47,600
That's for people who live
as subordinates their whole lives,

20
00:00:47,600 --> 00:00:49,700
chasing after it and clinging to it.

21
00:00:51,300 --> 00:00:52,500
Yeah, you're right.

22
00:00:52,900 --> 00:00:56,700
Justification is something
people like me need.

23
00:00:57,233 --> 00:00:59,700
Don't twist it like that.

24
00:00:59,800 --> 00:01:02,300
I'm offering
because I recognize your ability.

25
00:01:02,333 --> 00:01:04,800
Even so, there are principles.

26
00:01:05,400 --> 00:01:06,700
Anyway, decide within a week.

27
00:01:07,000 --> 00:01:08,300
There's already a vacancy,

28
00:01:08,300 --> 00:01:10,700
and if you just say yes,
you can start immediately.

29
00:01:11,133 --> 00:01:12,133
A vacancy?

30
00:01:14,133 --> 00:01:17,800
Don't tell me you're trying to put me
in Mr. Ju's position.

31
00:01:18,700 --> 00:01:21,200
Bingo. Mr. Ju agreed too.

32
00:01:23,100 --> 00:01:24,400
So that's why he...

33
00:01:25,400 --> 00:01:27,200
Why? Did he say something to you?

34
00:01:28,100 --> 00:01:30,100
Just ignore everything he says.

35
00:01:30,633 --> 00:01:33,300
You really don't know me at all.

36
00:01:34,200 --> 00:01:35,800
If it's that kind of position,
all the more reason I won't take it.

37
00:01:36,200 --> 00:01:37,433
Because of me, someone else...

38
00:01:37,900 --> 00:01:39,833
is losing their job
without a valid reason.

39
00:01:41,800 --> 00:01:42,800
I'm leaving.

40
00:01:42,933 --> 00:01:44,300
Hey, Seong Jun!

41
00:01:46,200 --> 00:01:47,900
Man, he's so prickly.

42
00:01:49,500 --> 00:01:53,033
Where is your arrow pointing, Ms. Cho?

43
00:01:54,233 --> 00:01:55,300
Well...

44
00:01:56,933 --> 00:01:57,933
Tell me.

45
00:01:59,100 --> 00:02:00,300
Where is your arrow...

46
00:02:01,233 --> 00:02:02,600
pointing right now?

47
00:02:07,133 --> 00:02:08,133
Come on.

48
00:02:08,800 --> 00:02:11,233
Say it.

49
00:02:18,133 --> 00:02:19,233
I don't have any arrow.

50
00:02:22,000 --> 00:02:24,433
If you don't have one, that's fine.

51
00:02:24,433 --> 00:02:25,833
You didn't have to push me!

52
00:02:26,800 --> 00:02:28,433
You kept asking when I don't have one.

53
00:02:29,233 --> 00:02:32,600
I'm sure you understood what I meant,

54
00:02:32,933 --> 00:02:34,033
so I'll get going now.

55
00:02:34,033 --> 00:02:36,100
I said let's have lunch together.

56
00:02:36,100 --> 00:02:39,033
No thanks. Have lunch with Manager Seo.

57
00:02:39,400 --> 00:02:40,900
Seriously, you're so clueless.

58
00:02:42,000 --> 00:02:43,000
Wait...

59
00:02:49,300 --> 00:02:51,600
I really can't figure her out at all.

60
00:03:00,400 --> 00:03:02,433
What? What's the annual salary?

61
00:03:03,300 --> 00:03:06,600
It's 80,000 dollars.
If you add overtime and bonuses,

62
00:03:07,133 --> 00:03:08,400
it'll come out to around 100,000 dollars.

63
00:03:12,900 --> 00:03:13,900
Dad.

64
00:03:15,000 --> 00:03:16,300
Hey, Eun Ae.

65
00:03:17,200 --> 00:03:18,300
Did you have lunch?

66
00:03:22,500 --> 00:03:24,200
(CPO, Manager Seo, Team Manager, Me)

67
00:03:27,100 --> 00:03:28,100
What are you doing?

68
00:03:28,700 --> 00:03:30,300
Nothing.

69
00:03:31,200 --> 00:03:32,800
Something interesting going on?

70
00:03:33,033 --> 00:03:34,133
No.

71
00:03:34,900 --> 00:03:37,800
But why the sudden casual speech?
We're at work.

72
00:03:38,033 --> 00:03:39,400
It's just the two of us.

73
00:03:39,900 --> 00:03:41,900
When it's just us,
I want to go back to how we used to speak.

74
00:03:42,700 --> 00:03:44,700
But what's this?

75
00:03:49,100 --> 00:03:50,533
Did Ms. Cho draw this?

76
00:03:50,600 --> 00:03:53,400
Well, she's always been a bit odd.

77
00:03:55,500 --> 00:03:58,700
She may be odd, but she seems
to have grasped it accurately.

78
00:04:01,933 --> 00:04:02,933
Tell me.

79
00:04:03,600 --> 00:04:06,400
Where is your arrow pointing right now?

80
00:04:08,533 --> 00:04:09,533
Come on.

81
00:04:10,500 --> 00:04:11,700
Say it.

82
00:04:15,400 --> 00:04:16,400
Seo Seung Ri.

83
00:04:19,233 --> 00:04:20,233
Just face it head-on.

84
00:04:21,033 --> 00:04:22,700
Avoiding it like this isn't like you.

85
00:04:23,800 --> 00:04:25,400
Where is the confident,

86
00:04:25,400 --> 00:04:26,900
bold Seo Seung Ri?

87
00:04:27,400 --> 00:04:29,333
Face it directly. That's who you are.

88
00:04:45,700 --> 00:04:47,933
I overheard your conversation by accident.

89
00:04:49,000 --> 00:04:50,300
The door was open.

90
00:04:51,400 --> 00:04:52,400
What?

91
00:04:53,000 --> 00:04:56,233
It seems like you're very curious
about Ms. Cho Eun Ae's arrow.

92
00:04:56,833 --> 00:04:58,433
But I'm curious about yours.

93
00:05:00,100 --> 00:05:03,600
Is it really like she said,
that maybe-maybe-not thing?

94
00:05:03,600 --> 00:05:06,100
Seo Seung Ri, that's just...

95
00:05:06,100 --> 00:05:08,200
I know you're not someone...

96
00:05:08,200 --> 00:05:09,733
who easily opens your heart to anyone.

97
00:05:10,600 --> 00:05:12,033
Yeah, that's enough.

98
00:05:14,000 --> 00:05:17,733
Gyeol, I'm hungry.
Want to go grab lunch together?

99
00:05:23,733 --> 00:05:25,000
This place is really good.

100
00:05:25,400 --> 00:05:27,033
How did you find a place like this?

101
00:05:27,033 --> 00:05:29,000
My manager recommended it.

102
00:05:29,233 --> 00:05:32,200
When I first joined,
she gave me all kinds of useful tips.

103
00:05:32,733 --> 00:05:35,033
Was it that same manager
who even bought you a welcome gift?

104
00:05:36,133 --> 00:05:37,900
You're lucky to have such a good boss.

105
00:05:39,033 --> 00:05:40,233
But these days,

106
00:05:41,033 --> 00:05:43,000
I think she's got it out for me.

107
00:05:43,800 --> 00:05:44,800
Why?

108
00:05:45,233 --> 00:05:47,633
What could you possibly have done
to get on someone's bad side?

109
00:05:49,000 --> 00:05:50,833
You're like a hedgehog.

110
00:05:51,300 --> 00:05:53,100
You're totally biased
when it comes to your kid.

111
00:05:57,433 --> 00:06:00,700
I gave you a shock, didn't I?

112
00:06:01,700 --> 00:06:03,933
When I brought up that thing
I'd kept to myself.

113
00:06:04,133 --> 00:06:05,300
Yeah, you rascal.

114
00:06:06,100 --> 00:06:08,600
If something like that happened,
you should've told me right away.

115
00:06:08,900 --> 00:06:10,900
Then you wouldn't have thought...

116
00:06:11,400 --> 00:06:13,200
your mom had abandoned you all that time.

117
00:06:14,900 --> 00:06:16,400
I think I was scared...

118
00:06:17,433 --> 00:06:19,100
to say it out loud...

119
00:06:20,633 --> 00:06:24,000
just in case it turned out to be true.

120
00:06:27,600 --> 00:06:28,600
My daughter,

121
00:06:29,733 --> 00:06:31,300
you held it in for so long.

122
00:06:32,100 --> 00:06:33,900
You must've been so anxious
all by yourself.

123
00:06:35,600 --> 00:06:38,433
You know what happened...

124
00:06:39,300 --> 00:06:40,800
with Mom that day, right?

125
00:06:43,900 --> 00:06:46,100
One day,
your mom will tell you everything,

126
00:06:47,433 --> 00:06:50,600
but before that,
there's one thing I can say for sure.

127
00:06:52,100 --> 00:06:53,100
That day,

128
00:06:54,733 --> 00:06:56,600
your mom never abandoned you.

129
00:06:59,033 --> 00:07:01,933
Okay. That's enough for me.

130
00:07:04,400 --> 00:07:07,000
But Dad,
do you have something on your mind?

131
00:07:08,600 --> 00:07:10,900
Why? Do I look like it?

132
00:07:11,100 --> 00:07:13,333
Yeah, you've been lost in thought
since I saw you in the hallway earlier.

133
00:07:14,200 --> 00:07:15,700
What is it? Tell me.

134
00:07:17,100 --> 00:07:19,433
It's nothing. Let's just eat.

135
00:07:20,633 --> 00:07:21,633
Welcome.

136
00:07:25,600 --> 00:07:26,600
Ms. Cho Eun Ae?

137
00:07:27,500 --> 00:07:28,500
Manager Seo.

138
00:07:30,533 --> 00:07:32,200
Are you here for a meal, Team Manager?

139
00:07:32,300 --> 00:07:33,300
Yes.

140
00:07:34,400 --> 00:07:35,933
This is my dad.

141
00:07:35,933 --> 00:07:38,100
Dad, this is my manager.

142
00:07:39,333 --> 00:07:41,700
Hello, I'm Seo Seung Ri.

143
00:07:41,833 --> 00:07:43,900
I've heard a lot about you.

144
00:07:44,400 --> 00:07:47,200
Thank you for taking good care
of my daughter.

145
00:07:47,933 --> 00:07:49,033
Are you joining them?

146
00:07:49,800 --> 00:07:51,433
No. Enjoy your meal.

147
00:07:51,433 --> 00:07:52,433
Yes.

148
00:08:06,433 --> 00:08:08,100
- Two soybean stews, please.
- Okay.

149
00:08:08,500 --> 00:08:11,200
The soybean paste stew here
is really good, Gyeol.

150
00:08:13,000 --> 00:08:14,300
Eat slowly.

151
00:08:14,700 --> 00:08:16,300
- Are you okay?
- Yeah.

152
00:08:36,833 --> 00:08:37,833
Move.

153
00:08:43,733 --> 00:08:44,733
Move.

154
00:08:51,300 --> 00:08:53,400
Won't you get up already?

155
00:08:55,033 --> 00:08:56,033
Mom.

156
00:08:57,500 --> 00:08:59,300
My whole world has collapsed.

157
00:08:59,300 --> 00:09:02,100
I don't have time
to listen to your pointless talk.

158
00:09:02,333 --> 00:09:03,600
Talk to the wall by yourself.

159
00:09:04,200 --> 00:09:05,500
I'm going to the Chairman's house.

160
00:09:05,500 --> 00:09:07,633
Get your own lunch, okay?

161
00:09:15,500 --> 00:09:18,433
All right.
Think about it logically, rationally,

162
00:09:18,533 --> 00:09:20,033
and seriously.

163
00:09:20,700 --> 00:09:22,800
"The ER Witch" is my all-time favorite.

164
00:09:23,100 --> 00:09:24,733
And if I were the one drawing it?

165
00:09:26,333 --> 00:09:28,200
That would make me
a true fan success story.

166
00:09:31,100 --> 00:09:34,200
But the writer is that crazy girl?

167
00:09:36,633 --> 00:09:38,333
You pervert!

168
00:09:41,700 --> 00:09:42,700
Seriously.

169
00:09:43,200 --> 00:09:44,200
What are you doing?

170
00:09:46,333 --> 00:09:47,400
I have one more hand, you know?

171
00:09:51,633 --> 00:09:54,133
No.

172
00:09:54,700 --> 00:09:56,300
No, do it.

173
00:09:57,000 --> 00:09:58,733
No, I can't. Do it.

174
00:09:58,900 --> 00:10:00,900
I can't do it! Do it!

175
00:10:02,700 --> 00:10:03,800
I don't know.

176
00:10:11,100 --> 00:10:12,100
Where did she go?

177
00:10:17,900 --> 00:10:19,800
("The ER Witch" Web Novel, Chapter 307)

178
00:10:21,200 --> 00:10:22,300
Mom.

179
00:10:24,800 --> 00:10:27,100
- When did you come in?
- Just now.

180
00:10:27,300 --> 00:10:28,600
Why? What's going on?

181
00:10:29,200 --> 00:10:30,533
Let's have lunch together.

182
00:10:31,200 --> 00:10:33,000
No, I'm going to the library now.

183
00:10:34,200 --> 00:10:36,633
By the way,
were you reading a medical novel?

184
00:10:38,000 --> 00:10:39,933
You're already busy preparing for exams.

185
00:10:44,333 --> 00:10:46,233
(Producer Park)

186
00:10:48,233 --> 00:10:49,500
Why aren't you answering that call?

187
00:10:49,500 --> 00:10:52,633
What? It's just spam.

188
00:10:53,733 --> 00:10:55,700
Mom, I'm going to change.

189
00:10:56,533 --> 00:10:59,300
Why are you being shy
in front of your own mom?

190
00:11:13,933 --> 00:11:17,200
Hello, Producer. What are you sending?

191
00:11:18,133 --> 00:11:19,133
A webtoon?

192
00:11:20,433 --> 00:11:22,900
I told you, I'd rather die
than work with that artist.

193
00:11:23,533 --> 00:11:25,600
Just take a look first, then we'll talk.

194
00:11:25,900 --> 00:11:26,900
Seriously.

195
00:11:28,400 --> 00:11:29,400
What the...

196
00:11:31,600 --> 00:11:34,500
What? "Secretary by Nature?"

197
00:11:36,733 --> 00:11:38,800
Even the title is awful. Totally awful.

198
00:11:46,000 --> 00:11:47,000
What is this?

199
00:11:47,300 --> 00:11:49,300
What do you think it is?

200
00:11:49,300 --> 00:11:52,933
Eun Hyeong's situation is more urgent
than Cho Rong's independence.

201
00:11:52,933 --> 00:11:55,033
I hope this can be a little bit of help.

202
00:11:55,833 --> 00:11:58,100
I appreciate the thought,

203
00:11:59,033 --> 00:12:00,700
but it's all over now.

204
00:12:01,700 --> 00:12:04,100
Eun Hyeong absolutely refused
to take that position.

205
00:12:04,200 --> 00:12:05,800
He already turned it down.

206
00:12:06,100 --> 00:12:07,733
My goodness, this is bad.

207
00:12:07,733 --> 00:12:11,400
I should've given you this earlier.

208
00:12:12,100 --> 00:12:13,300
That's not it.

209
00:12:13,600 --> 00:12:15,500
Even though we managed
to gather the money,

210
00:12:16,200 --> 00:12:18,100
Eun Hyeong said
he absolutely couldn't do it.

211
00:12:18,633 --> 00:12:20,700
Cho Rong was right.

212
00:12:20,700 --> 00:12:22,900
She said Eun Hyeong would never agree.

213
00:12:23,400 --> 00:12:24,733
Anyway, thank you...

214
00:12:25,900 --> 00:12:28,800
for worrying like family,

215
00:12:28,800 --> 00:12:30,400
and even offering money like this.

216
00:12:30,400 --> 00:12:33,233
Of course, that's only natural.

217
00:12:35,900 --> 00:12:39,300
But what will happen to Eun Hyeong now?

218
00:12:40,333 --> 00:12:42,300
It seems he's looking into other schools,

219
00:12:43,400 --> 00:12:46,500
but philosophy professor positions
aren't easy to come by these days.

220
00:12:46,733 --> 00:12:48,000
I see.

221
00:12:48,733 --> 00:12:52,500
Then why not open a fortune-telling shop?

222
00:12:52,800 --> 00:12:53,800
What?

223
00:12:53,900 --> 00:12:57,133
He has a PhD in philosophy,
so he could open a fortune-telling shop.

224
00:12:57,900 --> 00:12:58,900
Mrs. Park!

225
00:12:59,400 --> 00:13:00,233
What's wrong?

226
00:13:00,233 --> 00:13:02,500
They are two different things!

227
00:13:02,833 --> 00:13:06,300
Eun Hyeong has a PhD
from Hanguk University.

228
00:13:06,600 --> 00:13:08,533
He never lost the top spot in his class
until graduation.

229
00:13:08,700 --> 00:13:09,900
He's a doctor of philosophy.

230
00:13:10,900 --> 00:13:11,933
You should go.

231
00:13:18,900 --> 00:13:20,133
Where did you go, Grandma?

232
00:13:22,900 --> 00:13:26,300
I really can't figure out
what I did wrong.

233
00:13:28,400 --> 00:13:29,400
Joy.

234
00:13:29,733 --> 00:13:32,233
I'm genuinely curious.

235
00:13:32,900 --> 00:13:34,633
If a doctor in philosophy
opens a fortune-telling shop...

236
00:13:34,633 --> 00:13:35,633
Grandma.

237
00:13:36,433 --> 00:13:38,700
Don't tell me you told Eun Hyeong
to open a fortune-telling shop?

238
00:13:39,000 --> 00:13:43,133
Not Eun Hyeong. Eun Hyeong's mom.

239
00:13:43,133 --> 00:13:44,700
But was what I said wrong?

240
00:13:44,700 --> 00:13:45,800
She got really upset.

241
00:13:45,800 --> 00:13:47,433
Of course it was wrong.

242
00:13:47,433 --> 00:13:49,400
A philosophy department isn't the same
as a fortune-telling shop.

243
00:13:55,300 --> 00:13:56,400
Welcome, Jeong Ran.

244
00:13:57,200 --> 00:13:59,200
I heard about the Chairman, Madam.

245
00:13:59,500 --> 00:14:01,000
You must've been so shocked.

246
00:14:01,233 --> 00:14:02,700
Thank you for your concern.

247
00:14:03,500 --> 00:14:06,833
I'm so relieved he's recovering
without complications.

248
00:14:08,000 --> 00:14:09,633
What did you bring this time?

249
00:14:10,833 --> 00:14:12,400
I made some chicken and seafood soup.

250
00:14:14,300 --> 00:14:15,600
You didn't have to go this far.

251
00:14:16,700 --> 00:14:20,200
The Chairman won't be able
to eat regular food for a while.

252
00:14:20,300 --> 00:14:23,300
This is for you, Madam.

253
00:14:23,700 --> 00:14:26,000
You need to eat well
and regain your strength.

254
00:14:26,600 --> 00:14:29,000
Why are you going to such lengths for me?

255
00:14:29,333 --> 00:14:30,833
I hope it suits your taste.

256
00:14:32,300 --> 00:14:35,733
By the way, is Su Jeong not home?

257
00:14:35,933 --> 00:14:38,600
I don't know. I didn't hear her go out.

258
00:14:39,533 --> 00:14:43,733
I actually have something to tell you,
Madam.

259
00:14:44,100 --> 00:14:46,733
- Really? Then sit down.
- Okay.

260
00:14:53,500 --> 00:14:56,100
Yesterday,
when we heard the Chairman had collapsed,

261
00:14:56,733 --> 00:14:59,000
my husband was going to go
to the hospital right away,

262
00:14:59,633 --> 00:15:03,000
but Dae Chi said
outsiders weren't allowed.

263
00:15:03,233 --> 00:15:04,233
What?

264
00:15:06,400 --> 00:15:08,400
Dae Chi misspoke.

265
00:15:09,000 --> 00:15:12,700
You know how much
the Chairman relies on Gwon Sik.

266
00:15:12,833 --> 00:15:15,600
Of course, I know the Chairman...

267
00:15:15,600 --> 00:15:18,833
and you don't think that way, but still...

268
00:15:19,133 --> 00:15:20,133
My shoulder hurts.

269
00:15:23,200 --> 00:15:24,200
When did you get here?

270
00:15:24,933 --> 00:15:27,400
Sorry? Just now.

271
00:15:28,200 --> 00:15:30,700
Jeong Ran, I'll see you later.

272
00:15:30,700 --> 00:15:32,500
I need to go to the hospital.

273
00:15:32,933 --> 00:15:36,000
Would you like to take my car?
I'll drive you to the hospital.

274
00:15:38,300 --> 00:15:40,600
The car is ready, Madam.

275
00:15:40,933 --> 00:15:42,233
Excuse me a moment.

276
00:15:43,033 --> 00:15:46,600
This is chicken and seafood soup for Madam
since she's the caregiver,

277
00:15:46,900 --> 00:15:48,033
so please take it.

278
00:15:50,200 --> 00:15:52,733
You're more thoughtful
than their daughter-in-law.

279
00:15:53,300 --> 00:15:56,000
Mr. Ju, what are you saying?

280
00:15:56,833 --> 00:15:58,400
That's a bit much
for the daughter-in-law to hear.

281
00:15:59,900 --> 00:16:01,533
I didn't realize you were there.

282
00:16:02,500 --> 00:16:04,000
Let's go, Madam.

283
00:16:05,633 --> 00:16:07,800
Mother, have a safe trip.

284
00:16:13,900 --> 00:16:15,900
You know you're being obvious, right?

285
00:16:16,500 --> 00:16:18,000
Excuse me? What do you mean?

286
00:16:18,000 --> 00:16:20,000
You think I don't know
you're trying to butter up Mother...

287
00:16:20,000 --> 00:16:22,833
for the remaining 20 percent
of Father's shares?

288
00:16:23,033 --> 00:16:24,400
What are you talking about?

289
00:16:24,400 --> 00:16:27,600
Then why would you bring her
chicken and seafood soup?

290
00:16:28,300 --> 00:16:31,233
Isn't it because you're hoping
for some leftovers?

291
00:16:35,933 --> 00:16:37,233
Do you think you can just say anything?

292
00:16:38,433 --> 00:16:40,233
Do you think I'm as materialistic as you?

293
00:16:41,033 --> 00:16:42,800
To be honest, in terms of ability,

294
00:16:42,800 --> 00:16:44,200
isn't my husband a hundred, no,

295
00:16:44,200 --> 00:16:46,300
a thousand times better than yours?

296
00:16:47,100 --> 00:16:48,900
Don't act so superior just because...

297
00:16:49,800 --> 00:16:51,200
you were born into a good family!

298
00:16:55,900 --> 00:16:57,600
Why are you staring at me like that?

299
00:16:58,200 --> 00:16:59,500
If you have something to say, say it.

300
00:17:02,000 --> 00:17:03,000
I never...

301
00:17:03,700 --> 00:17:05,933
thought about leftovers of any kind.

302
00:17:05,933 --> 00:17:07,100
Of course you shouldn't.

303
00:17:07,500 --> 00:17:10,300
You wouldn't care try to get a share
of Father's stock.

304
00:17:10,300 --> 00:17:13,033
It's "dare," not "care."

305
00:17:13,233 --> 00:17:15,000
Right, how could you dare...

306
00:17:16,700 --> 00:17:19,000
Wait, are you scolding me right now?

307
00:17:19,400 --> 00:17:20,800
Over getting a four-character idiom wrong?

308
00:17:21,400 --> 00:17:22,700
- De...
- De toute façon.

309
00:17:24,800 --> 00:17:27,133
Anyway, I'm busy, so I'll be going.

310
00:17:30,200 --> 00:17:33,600
That's my line. Don't copy me.

311
00:17:35,100 --> 00:17:36,733
Now that we've narrowed down the concept,

312
00:17:36,733 --> 00:17:38,400
let's start making it more concrete
from tomorrow.

313
00:17:38,900 --> 00:17:40,200
Please look up references...

314
00:17:40,200 --> 00:17:41,800
similar to the ideas we discussed today.

315
00:17:41,800 --> 00:17:42,800
Yes, understood.

316
00:17:43,500 --> 00:17:46,400
I was worried we were
falling behind Team One, but as expected.

317
00:17:48,000 --> 00:17:50,000
It's thanks to the two of you
actively participating.

318
00:17:50,800 --> 00:17:51,900
Let's end the meeting here for today.

319
00:17:54,500 --> 00:17:56,500
The soybean paste stew here
is really good,

320
00:17:56,500 --> 00:17:58,300
Gyeol.

321
00:18:01,600 --> 00:18:03,033
Aren't you leaving, Eun Ae?

322
00:18:03,933 --> 00:18:05,033
What? Oppa?

323
00:18:06,000 --> 00:18:07,333
- What?
- What?

324
00:18:07,500 --> 00:18:10,000
Yes, I should go.

325
00:18:12,700 --> 00:18:14,800
Wait, Ms. Cho Eun Ae,
I need to talk to you.

326
00:18:16,000 --> 00:18:17,300
- Then I'll get going.
- Yes.

327
00:18:21,100 --> 00:18:22,133
What is this?

328
00:18:22,133 --> 00:18:23,133
A contract.

329
00:18:23,433 --> 00:18:24,966
It states that,
until the project is completed,

330
00:18:24,966 --> 00:18:28,200
you will devote yourself exclusively
to the retirement community.

331
00:18:28,533 --> 00:18:30,600
So if I sign this,

332
00:18:30,600 --> 00:18:32,533
you'll let me access the server
starting today, right?

333
00:18:32,533 --> 00:18:35,700
Yes, but make sure
you thoroughly review the back page...

334
00:18:35,700 --> 00:18:38,000
to see what happens if you violate
the contract before signing.

335
00:18:42,900 --> 00:18:44,000
This law and that law.

336
00:18:44,500 --> 00:18:47,000
You really seem to like the law,
Team Manager.

337
00:18:47,233 --> 00:18:48,700
Is the law there for nothing?

338
00:18:48,900 --> 00:18:51,533
This is the minimum safeguard
against people like you,

339
00:18:51,533 --> 00:18:54,100
who have ulterior motives.

340
00:18:54,733 --> 00:18:56,200
Fine, I'll sign.

341
00:18:56,400 --> 00:18:59,600
But once the project is finished,
this contract is automatically terminated.

342
00:18:59,600 --> 00:19:01,700
Of course,
that's stated in the contract as well.

343
00:19:10,733 --> 00:19:12,700
Good. With this, our contract is...

344
00:19:12,700 --> 00:19:13,833
The server. Give me the server password.

345
00:19:15,000 --> 00:19:18,200
Seriously,
were you that desperate for the server?

346
00:19:18,300 --> 00:19:21,100
Of course.
I'm finally seeing my baby Joy again.

347
00:19:31,500 --> 00:19:33,000
There, see? The password.

348
00:19:35,800 --> 00:19:38,433
I didn't ask you to type it for me.
I asked you to just tell me.

349
00:19:39,433 --> 00:19:40,433
Seriously.

350
00:19:41,900 --> 00:19:44,133
The password is too long,
so I typed it myself...

351
00:19:44,133 --> 00:19:46,700
in case someone with a single-digit IQ
like you couldn't remember it.

352
00:19:49,500 --> 00:19:50,500
Here.

353
00:19:51,233 --> 00:19:52,533
This guy, seriously.

354
00:19:56,233 --> 00:19:58,333
Joy, your mom is here.

355
00:20:03,800 --> 00:20:06,900
This handsome face with an oxygen tube...

356
00:20:08,300 --> 00:20:09,500
This won't do at all.

357
00:20:10,300 --> 00:20:13,333
Why? You look cool to me.

358
00:20:15,600 --> 00:20:16,933
Dr. Kim said...

359
00:20:17,400 --> 00:20:21,100
you can go home after another day or two.

360
00:20:21,700 --> 00:20:22,800
Of course.

361
00:20:24,000 --> 00:20:27,100
Ko Kang Su isn't that fragile of a man.

362
00:20:28,400 --> 00:20:31,800
I know. You're stronger than anyone.

363
00:20:33,400 --> 00:20:35,500
Jeong Ran brought
some chicken and seafood soup.

364
00:20:35,800 --> 00:20:37,600
Would you like some broth?

365
00:20:38,800 --> 00:20:39,800
Later.

366
00:20:40,933 --> 00:20:44,900
More importantly,
I have something to say to you, Yeong Hwa.

367
00:20:48,200 --> 00:20:51,233
There's a final image of myself...

368
00:20:52,200 --> 00:20:54,800
that I have in mind, Yeong Hwa.

369
00:20:59,600 --> 00:21:01,500
What is it?

370
00:21:03,433 --> 00:21:07,900
Promise me first that you'll do as I wish.

371
00:21:09,200 --> 00:21:10,500
Then I'll tell you.

372
00:21:11,800 --> 00:21:14,800
All right, I promise.

373
00:21:15,700 --> 00:21:16,933
Go ahead.

374
00:21:19,200 --> 00:21:22,833
I quit as CEO Ko's executive assistant.

375
00:21:23,900 --> 00:21:25,700
What? Why all of a sudden?

376
00:21:26,000 --> 00:21:29,100
It's not sudden. I told you.

377
00:21:29,833 --> 00:21:32,300
CEO Ko was thinking of bringing in...

378
00:21:32,800 --> 00:21:34,600
a brainy assistant to replace me.

379
00:21:36,433 --> 00:21:39,300
If it were anyone else,
I would've persisted,

380
00:21:40,233 --> 00:21:41,500
but since it's Seong Jun...

381
00:21:42,800 --> 00:21:45,000
What? Seong Jun...

382
00:21:45,500 --> 00:21:47,233
has been confirmed as Dae Chi's assistant?

383
00:21:48,400 --> 00:21:52,500
I'm not completely sure,
but CEO Ko has already earmarked him.

384
00:21:54,500 --> 00:21:56,400
Honestly, I like it better this way.

385
00:21:57,300 --> 00:22:00,100
Taking care of the Chairman
and helping with housework...

386
00:22:01,800 --> 00:22:03,233
were originally part of my job anyway.

387
00:22:04,600 --> 00:22:07,433
Still, it can't feel good.

388
00:22:08,100 --> 00:22:10,200
You've been serving CEO Ko
for over 15 years.

389
00:22:11,100 --> 00:22:12,100
Did you say 15 years?

390
00:22:14,600 --> 00:22:17,900
That's not even that long.

391
00:22:19,100 --> 00:22:21,500
I practically raised CEO Ko...

392
00:22:22,100 --> 00:22:24,433
since he was crawling around as a baby.

393
00:22:26,900 --> 00:22:30,433
There's nothing about him I don't know.

394
00:22:31,333 --> 00:22:33,433
Even things I shouldn't know.

395
00:22:36,033 --> 00:22:38,400
Seong Jun is tight-lipped...

396
00:22:38,400 --> 00:22:39,900
and trustworthy, that's what I mean.

397
00:22:39,900 --> 00:22:42,100
- What are you doing here?
- Hey.

398
00:22:44,333 --> 00:22:46,500
Don't you see
the "No Unauthorized Entry" sign?

399
00:22:47,433 --> 00:22:50,800
Why are you all camping out here
instead of waiting in the car?

400
00:22:51,100 --> 00:22:54,600
Why are we unauthorized? We're involved.

401
00:22:54,833 --> 00:22:56,033
Then what are we, family?

402
00:22:56,100 --> 00:22:58,300
Or are you medical staff?

403
00:23:00,400 --> 00:23:01,900
You look ridiculous
just sitting here like this.

404
00:23:04,300 --> 00:23:05,300
Hello?

405
00:23:05,700 --> 00:23:08,600
A photo? Understood.

406
00:23:10,333 --> 00:23:12,133
Mr. Ju, let's go.

407
00:23:12,900 --> 00:23:15,633
What? Fine then. You meanie.

408
00:23:17,500 --> 00:23:18,500
Meanie?

409
00:23:19,233 --> 00:23:22,133
He really crossed the line just now.

410
00:23:26,233 --> 00:23:29,933
The password to my safe
is that child's birthday.

411
00:23:35,633 --> 00:23:36,833
Stop talking.

412
00:23:37,633 --> 00:23:38,833
I'll go get Dr. Kim.

413
00:23:53,400 --> 00:23:54,400
That child's birthday?

414
00:24:00,100 --> 00:24:01,100
Mom.

415
00:24:01,400 --> 00:24:03,300
Welcome home, honey.
You worked hard today.

416
00:24:04,000 --> 00:24:05,133
Dinner's ready.

417
00:24:07,600 --> 00:24:08,600
Wait a second.

418
00:24:13,000 --> 00:24:15,200
Bit Na, can you go tell Mom something?

419
00:24:15,833 --> 00:24:18,300
Tell her that today's meal
is the masterpiece of Dad's cooking,

420
00:24:18,300 --> 00:24:19,400
so she has to eat with us.

421
00:24:24,000 --> 00:24:26,300
Mom, Dad says today's meal...

422
00:24:26,300 --> 00:24:29,233
is the masterpiece of his cooking,
so you have to eat with us.

423
00:24:30,300 --> 00:24:31,733
Tell him I'm not hungry.

424
00:24:35,100 --> 00:24:36,633
Mom says she's not hungry, Dad.

425
00:24:37,600 --> 00:24:39,733
Tell her she'll regret it
if she doesn't eat.

426
00:24:43,133 --> 00:24:45,033
He says you'll regret it
if you don't eat, Mom.

427
00:24:45,100 --> 00:24:46,700
Tell him that won't happen.

428
00:24:51,000 --> 00:24:52,600
She says that won't happen, Dad.

429
00:24:52,633 --> 00:24:55,400
Tell her today's meal
absolutely needs her evaluation,

430
00:24:55,900 --> 00:24:56,933
that I have to prove it.

431
00:24:59,433 --> 00:25:01,633
He says
it absolutely needs your evaluation.

432
00:25:02,000 --> 00:25:03,800
He says he has to prove it.

433
00:25:05,100 --> 00:25:08,133
If he makes me say one more thing,
I'm leaving again.

434
00:25:09,833 --> 00:25:11,233
Mom, Dad.

435
00:25:11,400 --> 00:25:12,900
What is it?

436
00:25:13,933 --> 00:25:15,333
Are you really going to keep this up?

437
00:25:15,900 --> 00:25:18,600
You promised you wouldn't fight again.
Why aren't you keeping it?

438
00:25:19,033 --> 00:25:21,200
Then I won't keep promises either.

439
00:25:21,800 --> 00:25:24,933
I won't listen, I'll throw tantrums,
and I won't go to kindergarten.

440
00:25:25,000 --> 00:25:27,033
I'll do whatever I want.

441
00:25:28,400 --> 00:25:29,700
I'm sorry, Bit Na.

442
00:25:30,400 --> 00:25:32,533
Yes, Mom and Dad were wrong.

443
00:25:34,200 --> 00:25:36,933
Really? You won't fight again, right?

444
00:25:36,933 --> 00:25:38,033
Of course.

445
00:25:40,300 --> 00:25:44,500
Honey,
I've sent out my resume here and there.

446
00:25:44,533 --> 00:25:47,400
I have a feeling I'll get good news soon.

447
00:25:48,133 --> 00:25:49,133
So...

448
00:25:50,800 --> 00:25:51,800
Wait.

449
00:25:54,600 --> 00:25:55,800
Hello? This is Cho Eun Hyeong.

450
00:25:57,700 --> 00:26:00,900
What? Starting Monday?

451
00:26:02,033 --> 00:26:03,600
Full-time, five days a week?

452
00:26:05,200 --> 00:26:07,433
Thank you.

453
00:26:09,000 --> 00:26:10,000
Yes!

454
00:26:10,800 --> 00:26:13,300
A lecture? Which university?

455
00:26:13,700 --> 00:26:16,300
Not even a part-time lecturer
but full-time?

456
00:26:16,300 --> 00:26:18,933
Congratulations, Dad.
You're not unemployed anymore?

457
00:26:19,100 --> 00:26:20,300
Hey, Cho Bit Na.

458
00:26:20,533 --> 00:26:23,400
"Unemployed" is not an appropriate word
for children.

459
00:26:23,600 --> 00:26:25,700
Okay, I won't say that.

460
00:26:25,800 --> 00:26:27,500
You're a professor now, Dad.

461
00:26:27,833 --> 00:26:30,600
So which university is it? Where?

462
00:26:31,100 --> 00:26:34,733
I'll be teaching somewhere for now.

463
00:26:34,733 --> 00:26:36,600
My fulfillment comes
from teaching students.

464
00:26:36,900 --> 00:26:38,400
That's enough for me.

465
00:26:40,833 --> 00:26:42,000
Thank you, honey.

466
00:26:43,000 --> 00:26:45,700
And I'm really sorry for everything.

467
00:26:46,400 --> 00:26:49,433
I guess I gave up too easily...

468
00:26:50,433 --> 00:26:52,300
on the idea of you returning to campus.

469
00:26:53,000 --> 00:26:54,500
- Campus?
- Yes.

470
00:26:55,000 --> 00:26:56,833
Yes, campus. That's right.

471
00:26:59,033 --> 00:27:01,300
(Kangsu Construction)

472
00:27:22,600 --> 00:27:24,133
I thought you'd left, Team Manager.

473
00:27:24,133 --> 00:27:26,300
I did, but I came back.

474
00:27:28,133 --> 00:27:29,800
Here, at least eat this while you work.

475
00:27:30,300 --> 00:27:32,500
Did you get this for me?

476
00:27:33,100 --> 00:27:36,333
What? No, it's just...

477
00:27:37,300 --> 00:27:41,033
I appreciate the thought,
but I don't have time to eat right now.

478
00:27:43,200 --> 00:27:46,100
Do you really like it that much?

479
00:27:46,333 --> 00:27:48,200
Yes, I do. Very much.

480
00:27:48,333 --> 00:27:49,933
I really like it, Team Manager.

481
00:28:11,100 --> 00:28:13,800
(Our Happy Days)

482
00:28:13,900 --> 00:28:15,600
- Cho Eun Nim.
- Eun Ae.

483
00:28:15,600 --> 00:28:17,233
- I dropped out.
- You dropped out?

484
00:28:17,433 --> 00:28:19,833
It has to be somewhere in this room.

485
00:28:20,000 --> 00:28:21,533
Who is that child?

486
00:28:21,533 --> 00:28:23,300
I asked if you liked Joy that much,

487
00:28:23,300 --> 00:28:25,000
and you said you did.

488
00:28:25,000 --> 00:28:27,900
Did you perhaps mean something else
by that?

489
00:28:27,900 --> 00:28:29,500
What? Even Dad and Eun Hyeong?

490
00:28:29,500 --> 00:28:31,833
Since it's come to this,
I'll just face it head-on.

491
00:28:32,433 --> 00:28:34,000
(Subtitles are provided by KOCOWA.)
